# Morph is BYOK (Bring Your Own Key): there is no shared/default provider key,
# so no server-side secret is required to run this project locally or in
# production. Each user supplies their own Gemini API key in the UI; it is
# stored in the browser only and forwarded per-request via the
# `x-user-api-key` header. See SECURITY.md for the full data-flow.
#
# This file is intentionally empty of secrets. Add a variable here only when
# a real server-side need arises (e.g. a rate-limiting store), and document
# why in SECURITY.md at the same time.
